meaning: Godot tried to create another instance of NavigationServer2D, but another one exists.
causes: A module or plugin is trying to create another instance of NavigationServer2D.
The initialization code for NavigationServer2D is being executed twice while the engine is starting.
A module or plugin tries to re-register NavigationServer2D even though Godot already registered it.
fixes: Ensure that NavigationServer2D is registered only once.
Remove any calls in the modules or plugins you have installed which may try to create another instance of NavigationServer2D.
If modifying the engine source, check for any calls to re-execute the initialization code for NavigationServer2D.
notes: This error normally does not appear in standard GDScript/C# usage.
NavigationServer2D is managed by Godot, user code should not cause this error to happen
